The '''Tripple AxialJunction''' is a expensiv but very speedy junction for special direction-crossing. 

[[File:en/Community/Junctionary/Tripleaxial.png|none|thumb|600px|Triple Axial Junction (simple)]]

{{en/Community/Junctionary/Junction Criteria|Expensive|3|1|0|0|0|0|1|1|0|0|1|||
*Handles a very large number of trains at a time.
*Uses special directions -> "Top vs Bottom" and "Left vs Right"
*Small Area needed (12x12) 
*Less or No sharp corners (see improved version) (for high speed)
*No Hills are needed (for extrem high speed)
*No Deadlocks / Jamming possible
*No Merging / Splitting of the lines
*Handling of single-lines and dual-lines possible. Thats the reason no Splitters/Mergers are implemented. Do it by your own wishes.
*Lines starting one level higher entering the junction than leaving the junction
}}

